[assistant] {"action":"advisory_preparation","summary":"No extra Maven dependency or Docker image is needed; vertx-web-client 5.0.1 brings the normal Vert.x/Netty stack transitively and can be meaningfully exercised against an in-process Vert.x HttpServer. Native runs on JDK 25 should preserve the Netty unsafe-access runtime system properties already used for 5.0.0 because 5.0.1 still resolves Netty 4.2.x.","deterministic_setup":[],"agent_guidance":"For native-image runtime tests on JDK 25/current-defaults, set runtime system properties `-Dsun.misc.unsafe.memory.access=allow` and `-Dio.netty.tryReflectionSetAccessible=true`. Tests can use `Vertx.vertx()`, an in-process `HttpServer` bound to `127.0.0.1`/port 0, and `WebClient.create(...)`; no external service is required.","risks":["If generated tests choose OAuth2-specific APIs, `vertx-auth-oauth2` is optional in the POM and may require a deliberate dependency decision, but it is not needed for core WebClient coverage.","The unsafe-access properties are a native/JDK-25 compatibility workaround; local Gradle and Native Image verification remain authoritative."]}
